[start section id="$final"]
Final Diagnosis
A.  Colon, sigmoid, resection:  Moderately (grade 3 of 4) adenocarcinoma forming a 4.5 x 3.4 x 1.0 cm polypoid mass in the sigmoid.  Tumor invades into and focally through the muscularis propria.  Lymphatic/vascular invasion is absent.  The surgical resection margins are negative for dysplasia and tumor (closest tumor free margin, 4.0 cm).  Multiple (35) regional lymph nodes are negative for tumor. [AJCC pT3N0]
B.  Rectum, distal ring, resection:  Unremarkable colonic mucosa identified. Gross examination only.  




[end section id="$final"]
[start section id="$gross"]

Gross Description
A.  Received fresh labeled ""sigmoid"" is a 20.0 cm in length portion of sigmoid colon with a 4.5 x 3.4 x 1.0 cm polypoid mass located 4.0 cm from the closest mucosal margin and 6.0 cm from the radial margin.  Deepest tumor invasion is 0.6 cm and tumor perforation is absent.  Multiple lymph nodes are present within the mesenteric fat.  There is a second polypoid mass 0.9 x 0.8 x 0.4 cm located 0.8 cm from the larger mass.  Representative sections submitted.  Grossed by HURST.

B.  Received fresh labeled ""distal rectal ring"" is a 1.5 x 1.5 x 1.0 cm annular fragment of pink-tan mucosal tissue.  Gross examination only.  Grossed by HURST.





[end section id="$gross"]